1: Song of ascensions. To thee dwelling in the heavens I lifted up mine eyes.
2: Behold, as the eyes of servants to the hand of their lords, as the eyes of a maid to the hand of her mistress, so our eyes are to Jehovah our God, even till he compassionate us.
3: Compassionate us, O Jehovah, compassionate us: for we were much filled with contempt.
4: Much was our soul filled with it, a derision of those living at ease the contempt of the proud.
